AIM:
    To study the fabrication of microchannels using PDMS (Polydimethylsiloxane).

APPARATUS REQUIRED:
    PDMS (Base and Curing Agent)
    Silicon mold
    Petri dish
    Oven
    Vacuum desiccator
    Glass substrate
PROCEDURE:
  1.Mold Preparation
    Fabricate a mold using photolithography (master mold).
  2.PDMS Preparation
    Mix PDMS base and curing agent in ratio 10:1.
    Stir thoroughly.
  3.Degassing
    Place mixture in vacuum desiccator to remove air bubbles.
  4.Pouring
    Pour PDMS mixture onto mold.
  5.Curing
    Place in oven at 60–80°C for 1–2 hours.
  6.Peeling
    Remove cured PDMS carefully from mold.
  7.Bonding
    Bond PDMS to glass substrate (using plasma treatment if available).
RESULT:
    The microchannel is successfully fabricated using PDMS and is ready for microfluidic applications.
